The paper deals with scene text recognition using deep learning, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of deformable convolutional layers also suggests a focus on improving the network architecture, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the experiments involve benchmark datasets, indicating a focus on evaluation and performance analysis, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
